reviews.text: Food was too salty. I ordered the chicken linguini, parrot shrimp, lobster bisque soup and lobster with artichoke dip and chips. There was no distinction of taste in each dish. Everything tasted the same - VERY SALTY!  How does the chef not taste the food and see its too darn salty and still choose to serve it to paying customers?  I used Door Dash for delivery and my food was as cold as a dog's nose when it came. I've had good experiences with Red Lobster in the past, however, this time was a major FAIL. I couldn't eat my food because of all the salt. Red Lobster, please have a meeting with your chef(s) and suggest that they DO BETTER.

No complaints. Got the 3 from the Sea for $15.99 and the food was good. I ordered the parrot shrimp, Caesar salad, and chicken linguini with a strawberry lemonade. Shawn was an OK server. The front desk host forgot to text me my seat was available, but no big deal. Glad I asked about the wait.

My grandson and I had a pre-Easter Day, today outing today.  Sports Zone then Red Lobster to celebrate spring break.  He had a blast at the Zone trampoline park.  Red Lobster was a 4 🌟  would be a 3 🌟 but the manager gave my grandsons dinner to us for free.  See my $38.00 dinner arrived way after two other patrons at two different tables that came after me was served.  Water, biscuits,  no salad....then the waiting game.  Ok then when our food arrived my lobster tale was cold 🥶 😩.   I said no croutons,  my salad had croutons all over it.  I asked for a manager, explained the situation and he discounted our dinner he too 8.00$ off naking my grandson's dinner free.  So I was ok with that, but we got to do better.  Food to dam expensive. Pay attention young people.

This is a follow-up to a previous posting from a visit to Red Lobster. The initial review expressed my disappointment in the food I received from Red Lobster. It was a to go order and the food was dry and the order was incorrect.  Red Lobster apologized and asked that I give them an opportunity to make it right.

This is dinner last night at Red Lobster (different location). We dined in. Service was good. The food was prepared well, not overcooked. We had calamari and stuffed mushrooms for appetizers. I had the Admirals Feast and he had Salmon New Orleans. I also enjoyed a Sunset Passion Colada with strawberries. Again, so much better than the first time. Thank you!

The Service Was Great And My Waiter Was Fast And Off The Chain Mad I For His Name But He Did Say He Just Started Been There Two Weeks And U Would Thought He Been There For YEARS But The Down Fall Was The Bathroom It Was Nasty And No Seat Covers They Need To Check The Bathroom More To Make Sure They Good For There Customers Rather Then That I Enjoy My Meal

I didn’t get the obvious displeasure of trying the food from this restaurant, because they canceled my order at the last minute…thank God! From the look of the posted reviews, I dodged a really bad experience. When several people, from different locations and time frames are still saying the same thing (i.e. the stinky smell, half cooked food, long delivery wait, multiple hang ups and rude attitudes), you can get the picture of what’s true and what isn’t. Thanks bc your reviews kept me from thinking to try them again later! THANK YOU! My first experience with this place is also my last bc I’m done.
Invited for Karaoke!  it was fun.chill place.  people were nice. Bartender was nice even if he was the Maître d', waitress, bus boy, bathroom  attendant..lol, all of that!
The food could be better, but this place is great!

When you drive up it is a little confusing.. You enter through a liquor store and walk through to a bar. I regularly go for karaoke. It is currently Thursday, Friday, and Saturday night from 9:30p-1:30a. The karaoke DJ is great and the people there are entertaining. It is really welcoming and a no pressure place to start if you have never done karaoke before. The food is ok and it is kind of expensive. There are plenty of pool tables and the crowd size varies. The drinks from the bar seem expensive but the ones I've had from the bar are pretty strong and I got more than I expected.

Excuse my french....RUDE AS HELL!

So mad about my experience that I'm doing a review immediately.  Called to grab some food because it's late and they are the only place open.  This spot is right up the street from me, but I called it in because they boast free delivery on orders over $15 (see attachment).  Since I knew we'd be over $15, why not save the gas?

So I called, first problem, I spoke to about three people before I could even order. No big deal, so a guy, I'm assuming he was a manager or owner of some sort asks for my order and address.  Here's what I ordered...a 12 inch Steak n Cheese and 4 wings with fries.  How much should that add up to...at most??  Maybe $15, maybe even $20?  Well check this out, I ask for my total because I was considering ordering a drink.  The guy proceeds to tell me $26!  Excuse me?  There is no delivery fee!  How in ever is it $26???  So I questioned the total given and relayed the information listed on line.  He then tells me "that can't be right..I don't know who Andrew's Bar and Grill is we are Andrew's Restaurant...My price is right I set it".  Once he said he would not honor the price on the site, he told me he was busy and to call another time and HUNG UP THE PHONE.

What type of customer service is this???? I am so disappointed because this place is so close to me and they have what looks to be a nice happy hour.  But I will never support this place and you shouldn't either.  One big ripoff!  Check out my screenshots from their website, proof is in the pudding.  Stay away!  And if you decide to order, make sure you get itemized information on the cost of everything.

If I could give this place negative stars, I would.

Worst sushi and ramen I’ve ever had in my entire life. Everything is imitation and has a disgusting smell. I ended up throwing everything away because I couldn’t stomach it. $30.00 wasted. I’m never coming back. I wish I had read the reviews first, especially the one about the employee handing food while handling her hair. Overall the worst food experience I’ve had in a long time.

First, we tried to order online. It did not work. When we got there, we ordered at the register and went and sat down while we waited for our food. I then watched in amazement as the young lady that had just taken our order, stood between the register and the food prep area. With her bare hands, she removed her hair tie and commenced to messing with her hair. She pulled it back several times and eventually re-applied her hair tie. She then went back to handing customers their orders. NEVER WASHING HER HANDS FIRST!!! I approached her and explained how that looked doing that in the service area including not washing her hands. Her reply “oh ok”
I was not impressed. Would not recommend and will not be back.

Delivery was pleasantly surprising! Monday burrito with the crab salad was very good as were dumplings & dreadlocks roll (which I think could use a name change as it’s kinda offensive honestly & not at all caribbean or african in flavor), excellent otherwise.
The food is good but I add it salmon and tuna and they did not put any of it and I pay extra for it.
There is an amazing place, I ordered chicken bento box,fast and delicious, I ll try the sushi next time.
Really like the katsudon. The curry is good, toppings pair well. Have eaten here 10+ times
The curry is delicious. I also tried the takoyaki and is really good at a good price.

A fusion of Korean and Mexican cuisines.
What an idea!
While all the ingredients were very fresh and tasty, the food was too salty overall.
Personally I can still enjoy very spicy or little bland tasting food, but no way of salty ones because salty taste kills all flavors.
It would be a perfect experience if the food was not salty.
The helper at counter was super friendly and nice.
Eating area was well maintained as super clean every where.

An absolutely amazing fusion of Korean and Mexican cuisine!  The bulgogi beef bowl with purple rice was delicious, Korean tacos with kimchi was amazing, and the crispy dumplings were out of this world!  I will definitely be a regular when I'm in town.

Had a funny interaction for a first timer, but the visit is worth it for the food! 😋 My fellow otaku classmate told me about this place because of the kawaii decorations. 😸 Cool hangout spot with delightful looking grub. The restaurant is part of a Asian food center— you can get boba, sushi, and other dishes nearby. As a vegetarian, I was recommended the vegan bowl and a vegan taco. 🌱 The bowl was filled with flavor, and lots of fresh ingredients. I would’ve enjoyed the taco just as much, if it wasn’t made on a corn tortilla(I prefer flour tortillas). 😖 Still, all the food presentation was pretty and the toppings definitely spoke for itself. 👍 If you’re a carnivore, there’s a lot of to choose from! Will prolly come back with my boyfriend so he can give the meat options a try. GGs ✨

This is from the spot Asian food hall, KOTACO, only at the campspring. The best taco I have ever had. I hope this will help other taco lovers. I order Grill ca-bay shrimp and bulgogi beef, the sauce is perfectly match to the combination. I’ll definitely come again. Time!!!

I ordered the Bulgogi Chicken tacos and they were delicious. I love how they double the taco shells, which makes the taco sturdy and easy to eat. The ratio of chicken to toppings to taco shell was perfect. I will definitely be back.

name: The Real Milk & Honey Eatery & Bar

reviews.text: I love a good brunch spot! Many people complain but I’m going to congratulate! Running a business is not easy, especially in the food service industry. This restaurant’s decor really is a whole vibe and the music is great. The staff are pleasant and the food comes out hot. I had the crab hash and I ordered a biscuit and eggs on the side because sis was a little hungry. The margarita mimosas get you where you need to be. 1, 2, 3 and you’re good to go! I’ve been a few times since they’ve opened and they’ve been consistently good. Prices are reasonable for quality of food. I definitely recommend. The DMV is infamous for brunch so add it to your list! My girls and I were all smiles when we left.

Great customer service and staff.  The pancakes were some of the best I’ve had since I was a child.  All the food was fresh and normally they don’t serve onions with their hash browns but they gave me green onions and they were on point.  My first time at this location. The atmosphere, music and art were inviting .  I would have gave the restaurant five stars. But, the air conditioning was not on and it was hot in the restaurant.

Uggggh I am STUFFED!!! This grub is so so good. I had the lump crab meat with hash. Literally every bite had good sizes of crab meat. The staff is super friendly.  We really love the atmosphere as well. Deon is our waiter. He was funny and AWESOME

I enjoyed my visit to this brunch spot! The place reminds me of an art gallery (the pictures displayed on the walls are available for purchase).  The DJ was playing good music and I really like our server! The food of course was amazing.  My only complaint is the mimosa tower, it was more juice than champ.  I would of course totally go back.

We stopped here one late Saturday evening and ordered two staples off of the brunch menu. We had the shrimp and grits and the smothered chicken and biscuits. The shrimp and grits were very heavy and overwhelmed by the sauce, but the cheesy grits themselves were perfectly cooked and were tasty. The smothered chicken was well seasoned and the biscuits were warm and fluffy. The service was kind and welcoming as well. We were surprised by how empty the restaurant was, but maybe it was just because of the time we chose to visit.

This Subway is trash. I would strongly recommend going to the one down the road at the Shell. Customer service is 10x better and they aren't skimpy with the portions. Also, the owner here will do everything he can to not honor coupons.

I love the customer service of the worker named Sameer at this Subway location. He NEATLY prepares the sandwich like a work of art. It was just amazing to watch him going through his motions. He obviously takes pride in his work. Subway needs to give him a promotion.  If you come to this location and your sandwich is put together as I described, it's probably Sameer.
Update on 7/17/2022:  I continue to enjoy excellent customer service at this Subway location. A shout out to Edgar who treated me with professionalism and thoughtfulness.

Very disappointed That was a very horrible sandwich no meat I paid for bread got two slices of pepperoni one have salami and a slice of provolone a little bit of lettuce and one slice of red onion and there was no oil at this location. The employees are so rude when you ask questions they ignore you and they don’t speak good English. Ever since the black guy left service has went down. Please don’t eat here because there going to make someone sick I also found a piece of hair in my sandwich. I am totally disgusted I will never eat here again. I feel robbed I really feel like I was robbed of that sandwich it was a bread they didn't even put the oil and vinegar on it and there was hair in it. They refused to make another sandwich.

EASILY! The cleanest and most organized Subway I have ever been to in my life. The staff were also overly nice, just unnecessarily polite. Price was a little higher than I'm use to but I'll definitely be stopping by this one next time I'm in the area.
The meat and veggies were fresh! Would return.

We visited about 3 weeks ago now. I had been wanting to go for some time after finding a review searching for places to eat. Small space with a bar, but very very nice. Absolutely loved the mural on the wall of people and places in DC-even saw a few of our h.s. friends on the wall! Had the pleasure of meeting the owner who was in that day. He was very nice and personable, staff was pleasant as well. We will definitely be going back, food was delicious.  Black owned, Native to Washington, DC

GREAT food and ambience. We first had their rich and thick chocolate milkshake. Super tasty, best I tried in a while. The burgers were great and the sweet potatoes were crispy. We couldn’t finish our meal. I would recommend this place and we are planning to come back.

A friend of mine invited me here for the event held every Monday night. There was music featured from a local DJ along with some local rappers that made it a nice party scene. While I was there I did the byo burger with onion rings, not what I expected at all. I highly recommend getting the burger@ sauce with anything you order because its just that good, but disclaimer it has a kick to it. My burger had lettuce tomato bacon burger@ sauce and it was soooo good. The onion rings may be the best I've had so far, they were seasoned perfectly and crunchy. My only complaint is the bacon had some hard pieces to it, but was still good.

Nice location and this place has great food and a friendly customer experience. The staff makes you feel very welcome and the music is perfect to chill and relax eat and drink for a first date or any occasion. I definitely will be back to try other items on the menu. We tried the delicious Apollo Burger...yummy!!

Stopped in from out of state on a work trip and found Apollo on my google maps so I figured I’d stop in. I Ordered The Apollo burger and I was able to customize it to my liking and it was AMAZING! Definitely would return next time I’m in town! All of the staff was super friendly and made sure I was well taken care of. Very clean eating area and bathroom. They also were playing some JAMS! 5 outta 5 stars hands down!

my husband and I absolutely love this restaurant. this is my second time reviewing because I feel like it deserves an update. I rated 5 stars after the first time we came here, about 3 months ago. now, we’ve been here over 10 times and the 5 stars absolutely holds up. we’ve been slowly rolling through their menu offerings and nothing has been a miss. the ingredients are high quality, the drinks are delicious, the prices are fair, the employees are friendly. but nothing compares to how truly delicious the food is. genuine, authentic Rome-based italian food that makes every other restaurant taste depressingly average. we are so glad we found this hidden gem.

Amazing authentic Italian food. My wife and I enjoyed the kale salad, calamari, pizza and cocktails. My daughter who is a very picky 3y/o, enjoyed her chicken tenders. We also took dessert home.  One of the  owners even stopped to say hello. Ignore the negative reviews. This is the real deal and I am so glad this is close to home. (Waldorf)

How have I never heard of this place before 😍😍 definitely a hidden gem. Pizza is outstanding and I’ve never enjoyed take-out pasta so much in my life. Sauced, seasoned, and perfect portions. Definitely my family’s new go-to 🍕 🍝

Not pictured: the delicious and decadent bombolini 😋🍫

Stopped in for National Pizza Day, Mr. B went beyond whats typical for Pizza Day. His customer service and this restaurant is what needed in the area.

This restaurant is one that I highly recommend to those in the area and anyone, wanting great authentic Italian food.

Sit at the bar while Nikki is working, tell her LJ sent you and experience a true Mixologist.   6 stars

The service was amazing. Food was fresh and service was quick. Big portions, flavorful food and a extremely helpful server. I'm not sure her name but she is extremely dedicated and worked hard to give us an amazing experience. I would love to stop in again.

First time here I had the Apolo burger with onion rings both taste great one of the best tasting onion rings that I've had the burger is more than enough.I will return soon....Customer service was the best.

The Korean steak taco was flavorless and the taco shell taste like dry flour.  Three pieces of steak cut in cubes the size of a penny.  Shrimp taco had no flavor.  Nachos were stale and cheese taste old. More food varieties would be nice and not just all the same food offered.
Great new culinary options! Asian fusion, Italian, Southern, New American themes etc all in one place! In my experience the service and food has been top notch at all the places.

Apollo you let me down, Shrimp scampi in a spicy red sauce, with one cherry tomatoe in the dish.....shrimp scampi is usually a garlic butter olive oil with seasoning...did not like your version sorry!!
The other items family ordered everyone liked...Chicken Alfredo...Pannini...so other items were good!
Nice food places, but not finished. Need larger signs for establishments.

This is one of my favorite go to spots! It’s a hidden gem. One of my favorites here is the fried green tomato sandwich. Amazing! They have a lot of different food options. A must try if you’re in the Camp Springs area and have a taste for some delicious fresh made to order food. The service is great and the owner is very in tune with his customers. I’ve been here when he was present and definitely walks around personally checking to ensure everyone is satisfied. I highly recommend giving it a shot! I will always keep Cori’s at the top of my go to list.

The decor looks great! The food was also great. We had the spicy creole salmon pasta, the chicken and bacon pasta, and the delicious cornbread appetizers. Everything was great and we even had leftovers. They only serve beer and wine at the bar which is ok for a chill date night but I wish they had a full bar. Service was good. We will definitely be back.

Happy this place survived the pandemic. This is the quiet place in the cut that people often refer to...it's unassuming, filled with nice decor, and has good food and great drinks. If you go in a small group or order ahead, you'll probably rate this place higher than I did. We were a group of 25-30 (practically filling the whole restaurant) and called ahead but they weren't ready. Despite this we only had one server. The dishes came out really slow. The server barely checked to see if we were ok and got a few orders wrong. She was sweet but clearly not prepared for a group of our size. Luckily the food was good especially those sidewinder fries, fried green tomatoes, and Mac n cheese. So good I forgot to take photos and just dove into the food.
Give them a try just pack your patience

This was a good place for Easter brunch. It does not have the fastest service but the entrees were worth the wait. The spinach dip, chicken and waffles, and salmon and eggs were brunch favorites in my group of foodies. The burgers had seasoned patties, the french toast was decadent and laced with liquor, the shrimp and grits as well as the fish and grits were also well received. We were critical of the fried green tomatoes and Mac and cheese starters not being southern enough--but we still ate them 😉. The surroundings, atmosphere, and R&B, jazz sounds made the experience very "grown and sexy."

Family I have found the "BOMB dot Com" food spot here in Southern Maryland. You got to try the food at Cori's Modern Kitchen". The service is good, drinks are 🔥 and the food is seriously DELICIOUS! I ordered quite a few things to sample.

The catfish sandwich made me want to slap my momma. The lamb chop appetizer was seasoned well, tender and tasty. The fried green tomatoes were Banging! I haven't had such a tasty meal that I didn't personally make in a while.

The bartender Terri was GREAT! The manager Eugene was wonderful. I will definitely be eating here again. Looking forward to it 4 real! Please check them out you won't be disappointed. ❤️

The staff were cheerful, helpful and friendly. The fried chicken I purchased here was way past fresh and obviously cooked in old oil. To add insult to injury it was incredibly overpriced. I love royal farms but this was by far the worst I’ve ever been to for food.
Coffee and customer service is good! Need to be better ventilated it's always warm in there.  And you walk out smelling like fried chicken lol. I love the self checkout and the reward points!!!

Today I ordered a pulled chicken sandwich order 668 mind you it was a wait on fries shanty had ample time to make someone's sandwich from a order after mine but after fries unloaded she dispurse 10 orders  before making mine. I told her I been waiting and I'm hungry she said the sandwich wouldn't have made itself.. but made one prior for someone after me.. This is not good customer service. As she should have done both sandwiches back to back not favor a guy whom chatted her up who  came after me. Won't be back

My CREW💖 Mr Walter T Darnell Ms D Mama Doris Omar paris  The Service is Over the Top⭐️⭐️⭐️ I love ❤️ coming here⭐️ The Service fresh food. We need security for evening shift
Strange ppl outside we hours but I love ❤️ my Auth Royal Farms 💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙
I love this royal farms...the employees are so nice and Asia is a breath of fresh air....

Food is good, it has it days. Cashiers are on the dry side, need to be more user friendly and not so dry. I just feel like at this time and day with all going on we should be ecstatic to be alive, well and working. Definitely be more appreciative of others as your customers and vice versa.

Every single time I come to this location, they are out of something. This is a new location with very light traffic, especially when compared to neighboring locations, so this shouldn’t be. This is happening well before closing time, so either whenever is responsible for inventory needs to do better, or the staff needs to continue cooking ingredients. This has happened during my last four visits, which is why I waited to see if it was simply a random, one day occurrence, or something continuous. You all are not reducing how much you charge for a bowl, so unless there are extenuating circumstances, which there are not, then the ingredients need to be there.
This chipotle location is nice. It’s clean and the food here is good compared to some other locations.

The staff is very nice, the restaurant is clean. Although the staff have clear gloves on, It's not sanitary when the scoop your food with the spoon and then use there fingers to help place in your bowl burrito., and there still touching other stuff. Also the chicken is really salty and we eat fat in almost every bite, almost as if it's not cooked enough or it's not a good quality of meat.

Consistently out of some kind of item, and most often it is the guac. A Mexican style take out should rarely if ever be out of such a staple item. I imagine it is because this is a new location and they limit their food supplies to cut down on waste; but who knows.  Most of the staff is very friendly, but there are one or two that could work on their customer skills, such as rudely griping at customers who didn't read or didn't see a sign on the door when walking in, such as: "exact change only if paying with cash." Rarely are customers going to carry around exact change for everything. It's the restaurant's fault for not keeping more cash on hand for such transactions; don't blame the customers. Why would you berate a customer who is there giving you their business? It's just bad management all around. But, the restaurant is typically clean, has quick service and more often than not has good service.
Nice place

Look, I get it. This Subway location is in a  not-so-nice Shell gas station, and that can be off-putting. However, once you start placing your order with  one of the employees, (as of right now Sajid or Mohammed), you know you're in for something special. They go above and beyond to ensure that you have the best Subway experience you can get. You can tell that they truly do have a desire to provide customers with the highest degree of Eating Fresh. The restaurant area is kept clean, they don't jack up their prices, they give good portions, and they get your order done as quickly as possible. And if it's slow, you can chat with them a bit. They have very cool life stories!

There has been a mix up.
This review is for Academy Ford in Laurel.
The service department staff is always courteous. Always a pleasant experience over the last two years. Repairs are completed in a timely manner. Jake, Al, and Brian are very knowledgeable and helpful.
In a very unlikely place, I generally dont like subway, but this location has good subs...... Sandwich prep area was kept clean and changed glove between every transaction.
Employees were nice, but they didn't have a lot of things that I wanted on my wrap. The bathroom was disgusting.
Bathrooms were absolutely disgusting! Didn't even use them. After the bathroom scene didn't want to eat the food!! Left as fast as we could!!!

The shrimp basket was so delicious!!!! The mac and cheese was so good make you want to slap somebody.  The Crab cake was worth the money, and the cheese steak was awesome.  I only ordered the first item listed, but my wonderful co-workers let me taste their food.  I had a buffet for real.  Big shout out to the owner.  I will definitely return.

Premium ingredients with fast, great service. I had the sliders, which were huge for sliders. Great mini burgets, very juicy.  I also tried the hush puppies and mac and cheese, most of those ended up as leftovers.  Nice cheesy mac and hush puppies, non greasy.  Well made great take out place, but has a few tables if you want to eat there.

Steak & cheese was so flavorful and tender.  The loaded fries with fresh cooked bacon and cheese finished me off. It really is a lot of food. The presentation was awesome. Couldn't wait to dig in, so I forgot to take a photo.

Zestyz is a unique experience. Its a clash between carry out and a great home cooked meal. The environment is inviting and clean. My favorite is the mumbo wings with macaroni and cheese. The red velevet waffles are out of this world. Best food in town, hands down. You won't be disappointed!
I Don't Think This Place is Even Open Anymore.
